+Every acceptance record must contain:
+
+- exact commit SHA;
+- UTC execution time;
+- Python and operating-system versions;
+- command or workflow run ID;
+- input manifest and configuration hash;
+- artifact names and SHA-256 digests;
+- pass/fail/incomplete status;
+- known exclusions and skipped tests;
+- reviewer and sign-off date.
+
+Secrets, raw prompts containing sensitive data, provider credentials, and private research inputs must not be included in artifacts.
+
+## 4. Gate A — PR consolidation and change control
+
+### Procedure
+
+1. Confirm PR #17 targets `master`.
+2. Confirm PRs #14 and #16 are closed, unmerged, and marked superseded.
+3. Confirm no other open integration PR contains a competing subset of the same commits.
+4. Record `master` base SHA and PR head SHA.
+5. Review the complete `master...head` diff, not only the last stacked delta.
+6. Confirm the branch is mergeable and contains no conflict resolution not covered by tests.
+
+### Acceptance
+
+- Exactly one integration PR remains open.
+- Full-history diff is reviewable.
+- No changes were directly pushed to `master` as part of consolidation.
+
+## 5. Gate B — static quality and source integrity
+
+### Commands
+
+```bash
+python -m compileall -q src/paperagent
+ruff check .
+ruff format --check --diff .
+mypy --config-file pyproject.toml
+```
+
+### Additional review
+
+- Search for import-time mutation, monkey patching, `eval`, `exec`, unbounded subprocess execution, secret logging, raw traceback exposure, and unsafe path writes.
+- Confirm broad exception handlers convert failures to typed, redacted boundary errors.
+- Confirm compatibility modules are re-exports only.
+- Confirm generated files are not silently treated as authoritative source.
+
+### Acceptance
+
+- All commands pass.
+- No unresolved P0/P1 finding.
+- Any suppression is documented with scope and justification.
+
+## 6. Gate C — offline automated tests and coverage
+
+### Command
+
+```bash
+pytest --cov=paperagent --cov-branch --cov-report=term-missing -q
+```
+
+### Required coverage
+
+- Python 3.11 and 3.12.
+- Branch coverage threshold at least the configured 90 percent.
+- New consolidated-review regressions pass:
+  - no import-time policy rebinding;
+  - synthetic readiness and release boundary;
+  - real-evidence controlled-experiment boundary;
+  - novelty-variant rejection;
+  - duplicate and non-finite contract rejection;
+  - verifiable provenance;
+  - full experiment fairness;
+  - unknown module and missing-loss rejection;
+  - observed SQLite journal mode.
+
+### Acceptance
+
+- Zero failing offline tests.
+- Skips are only for explicitly marked network, real-provider, browser, or credentialed tests.
+- Snapshot changes are reviewed and explained.
